[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "b847ca9bb06fd51a6a492754aff575fa366198c52ff0c50cf654062a4cc36b32"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_major"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST has 17 points counting 1 extra for the fifth \S. This is a middle-range hand with five \Ss. 
So he opens 1\S.

WEST only has 7 points, 6 in high cards and one more for the doubleton \D. 
But she does have three \Ss, so she can respond 2\S.

Since EAST is middle-range, he makes one more try by bidding 3\S.

If WEST had 9 or 10 points she would now bid 4\S - but with 7 she passes.}

